original_title: The Rolling Stones - The Biggest Bang: Zilker Park, Austin
overview: The Rolling Stones have played Austin just once before, in October 2006 at Zilker Park. More than 40,000 fans, plus many more who listened from outside the event gates, witnessed the rock legends playing an 18-song set as part of the band’s two-year world tour to support its 2005 album “A Bigger Bang.”
title: The Rolling Stones - The Biggest Bang: Zilker Park, Austin
